  "commentary": "With SPX at 6591 sitting between max negative gamma at 6580 (-13.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+13.1B), dealers are likely buying the current zone as they're short gamma below spot, creating mechanical bid support. The BREAKOUT regime with massive negative GEX (-37.8B) means any sustained move above 6605 or below 6580 will trigger amplified dealer flow in the direction of the break, as they'll be forced to chase momentum. Watch 6605 closely as the positive gamma wall - a break above turns dealers into sellers, while failure here keeps them as buyers into the 6580-6575 negative gamma cluster.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6580-6605 with explosive moves if either level breaks.",
